  "prompt": "How wax KVPY SX stream exam?",
  "response": "The Kishore Vaigyanik Protsahan Yojana (KVPY) was a national-level fellowship program in India aimed at encouraging students to pursue a career in research in the field of basic sciences. The SX stream of the KVPY exam was intended for students in the 12th grade who were aspiring to join undergraduate programs in basic sciences.\n\nThe exam typically comprised two parts, Part I and Part II, and included questions from Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, and Biology. Students had to attempt questions from three of these four subjects in Part I and any two in Part II, based on their strengths and future aspirations. The questions were designed to test the analytical and problem-solving skills of the students rather than rote memorization.\n\nThe difficulty level of the KVPY SX stream exam was generally considered to be high, as it required a strong understanding of fundamental concepts and their application. Preparation for the exam often involved a thorough study of subjects up to the 12th-grade level, along with practice in solving complex problems and previous years' question papers.\n\nPlease note that the KVPY program was merged with the INSPIRE (Innovation in Science Pursuit for Inspired Research) program as of 2022, and the exam structure might have changed since then. For the latest updates, it would be advisable to check with the official sources or the organizing institute.",
